adams.flow.control.Flow
	-annotation
	The webservice that allows clients to:\n- cross-validate classifier setups\n- train (and cache) classifiers with data\n- use trained classifiers to make predictions on \n- evaluate trained classifiers on test data\n- optimize classifier setup on a dataset (MultiSearch)\n- train (and cache) clusterers with data\n- use trained clusterers to cluster data\n- transform data with a globally defined transformer
	-actor
		adams.flow.standalone.CallableActors
			-actor
				adams.flow.control.SubProcess
					-name
					simple transform
					-annotation
					simply adds an ID attribute (of type STRING) and removes all NOMINAL attributes
					-actor
						adams.flow.transformer.WekaFilter
							-filter
								weka.filters.unsupervised.attribute.AddID
									-C
									first
									-N
									ID
					-actor
						adams.flow.transformer.WekaFilter
							-name
							WekaFilter-1
							-filter
								weka.filters.unsupervised.attribute.RemoveType
									-T
									nominal
									
	-actor
		adams.flow.standalone.WSServer
			-logging-level
			INFO
			-web-service
				adams.flow.webservice.WekaServiceWS
					-implementation
						adams.flow.webservice.SimpleWekaService
	-actor
		adams.flow.source.Start
	-actor
		adams.flow.control.WhileLoop
			-name
			keep going
			-condition
				adams.flow.condition.bool.True
			-loop
				adams.flow.source.Start
			-loop
				adams.flow.control.Sleep
	-flow-execution-listener
		adams.flow.execution.NullListener

